Quant Hub Engineering Handbook
04_REPOSITORY_STRUCTURE
Document ID: QH-004Version: 1.0 DraftStatus: Draft
Purpose
Define the canonical repository layout for Quant Hub. Every source file, configuration, document, test, asset, and future module must conform to this structure.
Repository Philosophy
The repository shall be organized by responsibility rather than file type.Every directory has a single purpose.No miscellaneous folders are permitted.
Top-Level Layout
QuantHub/│├── docs/├── backend/├── frontend/├── data/├── strategies/├── research/├── ml/├── infrastructure/├── scripts/├── tests/├── configs/├── docker/├── logs/├── assets/├── notebooks/├── .github/└── README.md
Directory Responsibilities
docs/ : Engineering handbook and ADRsbackend/ : Core APIs and business servicesfrontend/ : Dashboard UIdata/ : Data ingestion and storage logicstrategies/ : Strategy plugins (e.g., Lancaster)research/ : Experimental quantitative researchml/ : Machine learning pipelinesinfrastructure/ : Deployment and DevOpstests/ : Unit, integration and regression testsconfigs/ : Configuration filesscripts/ : Automation utilitiesdocker/ : Containers and compose fileslogs/ : Runtime logs (gitignored)assets/ : Icons, images and brandingnotebooks/ : Exploratory research only
Repository Rules
• No business logic inside scripts/• No experiments inside production modules• No secrets committed to Git• Documentation updated with structural changes• Each module owns its own README where appropriate
Naming Standards
Directories: lowercase_snake_casePython modules: snake_caseClasses: PascalCaseFunctions: snake_caseConstants: UPPER_CASEConfiguration files: descriptive lowercase
Future Growth
Repository structure must accommodate:• Additional exchanges• Additional strategies• Multiple asset classes• Cloud services• AI tooling• Plugin marketplacewithout restructuring the repository.
Closing
The repository structure is an architectural contract. Consistent organization reduces maintenance cost, simplifies onboarding, and supports long-term scalability.